<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Shout2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Shout,</orth> vb. to cry in exultation: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.87" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.4.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 4, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 79</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 79</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 79</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jc 5.3.32" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.12.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 12, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 56</bibl>. With <cit><quote>out:</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 103</bibl></cit>. With an accus. of the effect: <cit><quote>--ing their emulation,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.218" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 218</bibl></cit> (showing by shouts). <cit><quote>you s. me forth in acclamations hyperbolical,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.50" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 9, 50</bibl></cit> (O. Edd. <emph>shooting</emph> and <emph>shoot</emph> in the two last passages). cf. <emph>Unshout.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>